n civil society: even where membership numbers are in decline and societal plurality is on the rise, the contribution made by the church to social cohesion remains central in both town and country. This poses of the question of how the church in flux contributes and can continue to contribute to the different manifestations of social cohesion in urban and rural contexts.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aGleichwertige Lebensverhältnisse. 4aKirchen im Wandel. 4aKirchen. 4aLändliche Räume. 4aSoziale Institution. 4aSoziale Kohäsion. 4aStadt.  aChurches.  achurches in flux.  acity.  aequality of living conditions.  arural spaces.  asocial cohesion.  asocial institution.1 aBär, Martina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFaix, Tobias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrönlund, Henrietta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHoyer, Birgit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeireis, Torsten, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMenzel, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWustmans, Clemens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWustmans, Clemens, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZarnow, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2022z9783110994537oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107747880 cprintz978311077406140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311077468940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110774